I<sub>1</sub>=&radic;<span style="text-decoration:overline">(P/R1)</span>;<br>U fiind aceeasi pe R<sub>1</sub> si R<sub>2</sub>, R<sub>1</sub>I<sub>1</sub>=R<sub>2</sub>I<sub>2</sub> deci I<sub>1</sub> / I<sub>2</sub> = R<sub>2</sub> / R<sub>1</sub>, aflam I<sub>2</sub>, il adunam cu I<sub>1</sub> ajungem la rezultat.<br>Mai simplu: Folosind regula divizorului de curent [ I<sub>1</sub> = I * R<sub>2</sub> / (R<sub>1</sub>+R<sub>2</sub>) ], I = I<sub>1</sub>*(R<sub>1</sub>+R<sub>2</sub>) / R<sub>2</sub> = &radic;<span style="text-decoration:overline">(16/100)</span> * 300 / 200 = <b>0.6[A]</b>
YO6OWN, Brasov, 2007
